{
  "stem": "1799.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Actually at that point it was called a home.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was not a true orphanage.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I must go back to the platform at the train station in Paris.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When, when this transport arrived, I saw my father there, even though I was told that he had to be somewhere in southern France to take his ship.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But he was at the train station.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And a cousin, my mother's cousin was there as well.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it felt good for me to see my dad.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I hadn't seen him since the day he was arrested in October of the previous year.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was very warm.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I asked him that-- what do we do now?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "On the train already and elsewhere, there was no kosher food.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he said, at times like this, this is excusable.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You have no choice, just be careful.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And matter of fact, there was no real kosher food.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Even though it was a Jewish home, it was not a kosher-type home.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the other thing I must mention-- might not be that relevant, but I will mention it-- is at the train, we had checked in the bicycle that I had received for my bar mitzvah the previous year, to take with me, but they didn't bring it across the border.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was left behind in [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Zweibrucken, ?] which is the border town from Germany to France.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was very concerned about not having the bike.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And two or three days later, my aunt, or the cousin that I mentioned, had gone to retrieve the bike, paying the duty, which had not been paid.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I ended up with the bike in that home.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I was the only boy in that home that had a bicycle.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
